data.enText: to sing a tune with your lips closed
She was humming softly to herself.
to make a low continuous sound
The streets were beginning to hum with life.

data.chText: 犹豫不决；支支吾吾；嗯嗯呃呃
data.enText: to take a long time to make a decision or before you say sth

data.chText: 蜜蜂的嗡嗡声；车辆的呜呜声；人的嘈杂声
房间里充满了嘈杂的谈话声。
data.enText: The room filled with the hum of conversation.

means: 哼!（表示轻蔑、踌躇、怀疑等）

data.chText: 犹豫不决；支支吾吾；嗯嗯呃呃
data.enText: to take a long time to make a decision or before you say sth

tr: the state of being or appearing to be actively engaged in an activity
example: they manifested all the busyness of a pack of beavers
there is a constant hum of military preparation
This office is buzzing with activity

value.def: If something hums, it makes a low continuous noise.

example.ex: The birds sang, the bees hummed...
Within five hours, the equipment will be humming away again...
example.tran: 用不了5小时，设备就又能嗡嗡地运转了。

example.ex: There was a low humming sound in the sky.
example.tran: 空中传来一阵低沉的嗡嗡声。

example.ex: There was a general hum of conversation around them.
example.tran: 他们周围的人都在嗡嗡地低声交谈。

value.tran: 发出连续而低沉的声音;发嗡嗡声

value.def: When you hum a tune, you sing it with your lips closed.

example.ex: She was humming a merry little tune...
example.tran: 她哼着一支欢快的小曲儿。

example.ex: He hummed to himself as he opened the trunk.
example.tran: 他独自哼着曲子打开了车子的后备箱。

example.ex: The guard stopped his humming and turned his head sharply.
example.tran: 守卫停止了哼唱，猛地转过头。

value.def: If you say that a place hums, you mean that it is full of activity.

example.ex: The place is really beginning to hum...
example.tran: 这个地方真正开始热闹起来了。

example.ex: On Saturday morning, the town hums with activity and life.
example.tran: 周六早晨，小镇一派热闹繁忙，活力盎然。

value.def: Hum is sometimes used to represent the sound people make when they are not sure what to say.

example.ex: Hum, I am sorry but I thought you were French.
example.tran: 嗯，很抱歉，我以为你是法国人。

trans: 沉闷乏味的;无聊的;平淡无奇的
支支吾吾;吞吞吐吐;嗫嚅
